  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "With trumpet and sound of cornet,.... The Septuagint, Vulgate Latin, and Ethiopic versions, render it ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "with ductile trumpets, such as were made of silver, as the two trumpets for the calling of the assembly, Numbers 10:2 to which the allusion seems to be here, called \"asosra\" by Josephus (c) according to the Hebrew language  which he says were in length a little less than a cubit, but the pipe narrow, somewhat thicker than a flute, having a sufficient breadth at the mouth to blow with, ending after the manner of a bell. The cornet was a trumpet or pipe, made of horn, from whence it has its name; such were those, made of rams' horns, the priests blew with when they encompassed Jericho, Joshua 6:4, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "with ductile trumpets, such as were made of silver, as the two trumpets for the calling of the assembly, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 10:2",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " to which the allusion seems to be here, called \"asosra\" by Josephus (c) according to the Hebrew language  which he says were in length a little less than a cubit, but the pipe narrow, somewhat thicker than a flute, having a sufficient breadth at the mouth to blow with, ending after the manner of a bell. The cornet was a trumpet or pipe, made of horn, from whence it has its name; such were those, made of rams' horns, the priests blew with when they encompassed Jericho, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Joshua 6:4",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "make a joyful noise before the Lord, the King; or rather \"before the King, the Lord\" (d); before the King, who is Jehovah, who is the King of kings, and Lord of lords; let this shout be made before him, in his presence, and on account of his kingly office, and because of some eminent appearance of his kingdom and glory; see Revelation 19:6. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "make a joyful noise before the Lord, the King; or rather \"before the King, the Lord\" (d); before the King, who is Jehovah, who is the King of kings, and Lord of lords; let this shout be made before him, in his presence, and on account of his kingly office, and because of some eminent appearance of his kingdom and glory; see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Revelation 19:6",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(c) Antique. Jud. l. 3. c. 12. sect. 6. (d)   \"coram rege Domino\", Pagninus, Tigurine version; so Junius & Tremellius, Piscator, Cocceius. ",
        "children": [
          {
